President Obama called members of the San Francisco Giants organization to congratulate them on winning the World Series. He expressed his excitement and recalled the White Sox breaking their own World Series dry spell. The President enjoyed watching the game and commended the team, including the pitching staff and young stars Madison Bumgarner and Buster Posey, for their composure under pressure. He also expressed curiosity about closer Brian Wilson's famous beard. The Giants invited the President to a home game, and he expressed his eagerness to personally congratulate the team at the White House.